## Critical Constraints

| Language | NEVER Do This |
|----------|---------------|
| **TypeScript** | `any` type, `as any`, `console.log`, `var`, circular imports |
| **Python** | bare `except:`, `from x import *`, string SQL concatenation, mutable defaults |
| **All** | hardcoded secrets, skip tests before deploy, God objects, layer violations |

## Architecture Rules

| Rule | Reason |
|------|--------|
| [e.g., All external requests via API layer] | Single entry point |
| [e.g., UI -> API -> Service -> Repository -> Data] | Layer isolation |
| [e.g., Dependencies via constructor injection] | Testability |
| [e.g., External services wrapped in adapters] | Swappable implementations |
| [e.g., Database changes require migrations] | Data integrity |

